cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the social network of a fanfiction community. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper explores the behavior of the community members. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper discusses factors that explain the popularity of authors in the community. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper touches on aspects of the community that relate to human behavior and interaction. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing written text in the form of fanfiction stories.
